HEADWORD: Pernyi moth
<hw>Per"ny*i moth"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
silk-producing moth (<spn>Attacus Pernyi</spn>) which feeds upon the
oak. It has been introduced into Europe and America from
China.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

